TextBody:
Hi Peter,

Thank you for reaching out to Netwrix support regarding your issue. I would be happy to assist you. By accessing the query properties of the FSAA system scan job you can perform a reset of the filesystem data. This can be accessed under the maintenance tab within the query properties. Once the reset has been completed please run the FSAA bulk import once more.

If you would like to schedule a meeting you may use the link below:

https://nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=mSf3gWMwaJ22P_mQvWH0PM8FZQMXATVUhHQ5inlAipw-Z&MeetingID=iGVLAIkHfpNXSTwjrgm2v.jLhuwsotBLFQi_RTkNagc-Z

Thank you,

Scottie Taylor
Technical Support Engineer

TextBody:
Hi Peter,

Thank you for attending our scheduled meeting today. We discovered that the FSAA Bulk import was failing due to a permissions-based issue occurring on the update statistics SQL script for the analysis task. I recommend providing the service account used in the job with this permission and running the bulk import again. 

Please provide an update on the results of the bulk import. 

Thank you,

Scottie Taylor
Technical Support Engineer
